o work harder?\"\n\nAmamiya Noriko clicked her tongue, \"You can eat a bento when you go up.\"\n\nDr. A Li seemed to be on adrenaline, and instantly escaped from the state of being out of breath.\n\nA few people quickened their speed, and when they reached a platform on the mountain, they spread out a tablecloth under a big cherry tree. Xiaolan and Yuanzi took the dishes with great interest. Dr. A Li was full of expectations.\n\nKudo Shinichi watched Amamiya Noriko take out the binoculars from her backpack and looked at the guardrail. You are really ready!\n\nHe walked over to ask Amamiya Noriko what she saw, but heard Amamiya Noriko muttering in a low voice.\n\n\"If those guys at school saw me in such pink cherry blossoms, they would definitely want to fall in love, wouldn\'t they confess? If they all refused...\"\n\nKudo Shinichi held his forehead with one hand: \"Can you let go of your hobbies first?\"\n\nAmamiya Noriko glanced at him: \"One day I will arrest you to confess and refuse.\"'),
(402, 5, 22, 'Chapter 21: : The dangers of spring outing', 'In the blink of an eye, half a month has passed since the start of school.\n\nIn addition to the Chinese language, the first-year courses for Amamiya Noriko are all paediatrics, and the language is divided into modern and ancient. Amamiya Noriko opened her mouth to be in 18th grade Chinese, but Japanese stood on the same starting line as the others.\n\nElementary school occasionally misunderstands rhetoric and makes jokes.\n\nNow I can almost master the spoken language with my learning ability, but I still have to memorize and learn the ancient Japanese poetry.\n\nNext is history. History is divided into world history and Japanese history. She can do world history again, and Japanese history has to be relearned.\n\nBy the way, Amamiya Noriko\'s maths is a full-level grade, and her learning ability has been greatly improved in this regard.\n\nIn terms of home class, her Japanese cuisine is average, and she can do whatever she wants with Chinese cuisine.\n\nAs for the rest of the arts, music, social physics, geography, and so on, although everyone has just risen from elementary school, she is obviously not a normal person.\n\nAfter a quiz, she also ranked first in the whole class.\n\nSonoko looked at the ranking and sighed, \"It\'s the same as in elementary school.\"\n\nXiaolan nodded: \"At the top is Kiko.\"\n\nAmamiya Noriko was embarrassed: \"The language is still the same.\"\n\nKudo Shinichi looked at her test paper and nodded, \"It\'s still the same mistake in an outrageous place.\"\n\nThere were too many people looking at the rankings, so Amamiya Noriko could only glance sideways at Kudo Shinichi, and whispered embarrassingly, \"If only Shinichi could help me with some guidance.\"\n\n\"Shh—\"\n\nThe boys who were watching the rankings turned their attention to Kudo Shinichi. Why did Amamiya-san ask him to tutor him? And is it so close to directly call it by name?\n\nShin Kudo pulled Xiaolan over without