(470, 5, 37, 'Chapter 36: : Idol, autograph!', 'With excitement, Amamiya Noriko asked for an autograph from the idol Gin, whom she had admired for a long time.\n\nJin Jiu replied to her expressionlessly: \"Go away.\"\n\n  \"OK!\"\n\nAmamiya Noriko\'s heart was ready to complete the task and clear the suspicion, but she felt that Gin\'s autograph could still be won, it was quite memorable and could be framed.\n\nBy the way, Gin\'s real name is Kurosawajin. In the animation, when he went to a place called Mermaid Island to investigate the elixir of life, he left his real name on the list of tourist attractions.\n\nThe real name of Vodka, the driver of Gin, has also been left behind, Saburo Uozuka.\n\nAmamiya Noriko knew, but she didn\'t expect Gin to keep her real name, so she would be very interested to see what Gin would sign.\n\nSo Jin Jiu told her to go away, she said ok in her heart, but said seriously: \"Although I don\'t know which star you are, uncle, but I am definitely a fan of uncle.\"\n\nGin\'s eyes were cold and ruthless under the brim of his hat, and the aura he exuded made all the guests passing by shudder, and asked the waiter if the air conditioner was turned on too low?\n\nBut the little girl in front of her didn\'t feel the same at all. Instead, she muttered to the person next to her, \"Isn\'t the air conditioner cold? It feels a lot cooler.\"\n\nSitting on the seat, Jin Jiu raised his head slightly, and observed the little girl\'s face, her cheeks were white and flushed, and her eyes were not fully focused, but rather scattered.\n\nGenerally speaking, people who have a lot of high fever will do this, because if they focus their eyes and look serious, they will affect the scalp and cause headaches that accompany the fever, so they will subconsciously relax their eyes and appear not very energetic.\n\nJin Jiu glanced at her and retracted her gaze, which also explained why she wore a mask when looking at herself before.\n\nDo you really have an appetite to eat so much meat when you have a high fever?\n\nGin, who has basically no experience with colds and fevers, can\'t figure this out.\n\nBut he still said coldly: \"Go away, I\'m not a star.\"\n\nAmamiya Noriko gave him a thumbs up: \"Humble, uncle, you are too modest.\"\n\nWho doesn\'t know you as a Conan fan? The comic circulation of \"Detective Conan\" has already exceeded 200 million.\n\nGin was expressionless.\n\nAmamiya Noriko whispered, \"Don\'t worry, uncle, I don\'t think it\'s going to tell others that you are here. It will be troublesome for your other fans to know about it, right?\"\n\nGin took over her pen and paper, drew it in one stroke, then put it on the table with a banknote and got up and left.\n\nAmamiya Noriko thought he had given in, but when she turned her head, she saw a large vodka in a black suit and sunglasses at the door of Sukiyaki.\n\nAmamiya Noriko waved to Vodka with a kind smile.\n\nUnder the dark sunglasses, Vodka gave her a puzzled look.\n\nIn the underground parking lot of the mall, vodka and gin are on a black Porsche 356A.\n\nWhen Vodka started, she couldn\'t help but curiously said, \"Big brother, that little girl in the sukiyaki shop...\"\n\nJin Jiu interrupted coldly and said, \"Don\'t pay attention to her, how about the surveillance?\"\n\n\"No problem, the big brother broke it an hour before he started. I\'ve been watching it, and it hasn\'t been fixed yet.\"\n\n  \"Walk.\"\n\nGin expressionlessly lit the cigarette he was holding with the cigarette lighter.\n\nIn a sukiyaki shop.\n\nAmamiya Noriko looked at the signature on the note. The dragon was flying and the phoenix danced, the rather gorgeous \"Gin\", the English name of the gin sign.\n\nAlthough it is not his real name, it is also worth collecting.\n\nChieda Riho also settled the bill. When leaving the sukiyaki shop, Amamiya Noriko also took the opportunity to go to the guardrail to see what was going on under the mall.\n\nThe shape of the shopping mall is similar